You ever had a message come RIGHT on time?

Yesterday I was reminded of the serenity prayer. Not even 24 hrs later I received unfortunate, mostly annoying and inconveniencing, news. My default reaction would be to stress (and I’m not gone lie I did for a smooth 15 minutes). But I then remembered that all I can do is what I can do. The rest isn’t up to me.

God, grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change, courage to change the things I can, and wisdom to know the difference.

Three things you’ll always find in my closet:

1. Vintage / thrifted pieces. I know the girls are all about luxury these days, but I still really enjoy thrifting and shopping consignment, too. It’s cute for my closet AND my bank account.
2. Baggy clothes. Give me cargos. sweatpants. sweatshirts. t-shirts. I used to think that since I’m petite I couldn’t wear baggy clothes. But I’ve been freed from the shackles of “fashion rules” and idc idc idc if I look like an adorable little boy as long as I’m comfortable 😭 and adorable lol
3. Green. There’s just something about the color green that’s fun yet timeless.

I say all that to say, dis my OOTD.

Date Night 🖤

It’s funny when you move into a new house. You’re so excited to decorate, and buy new things, and fill the space. Eager to make it a home.

But there’s a point when you just stop. Maybe it’s to evaluate and reevaluate what you’ve done with the space thus far. Maybe your bank account became the enemy of progress. Maybe you, like me, decided to plan a wedding in five months so decorating took several backseats. Whatever the reason, the great thing about slowing down is that it allows you the chance savor and admire each new addition. Like getting these gorgeous pleated linen curtains in our bedroom almost 12 months into living here. I’ve pulled them open and shut countless times because, man does it feel good to finally have curtains 😂

P.S. please don’t ask me anything about a wedding or wedding planning. It’s ghetto here and I -10/10 recommend. Elope!
